The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Surya starts with win
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Surya starts with win
                      
	Dresden: Grandmaster and national champion Surya Shekhar Ganguly gave Indian men a winning start, defeating Pascal Charbonneau of Canada in the first round of the Chess Olympiad here.         
	Riding on Gangulys victory, the Indian men started off with a marginal 2.5-1.5 victory over Canada.         
	Ganguly was the lone winner among Indian men as P. Harikrishna, Sandipan Chanda and G.N. Gopal were held to draws by lower-rated opponents.         
	The Indian womens team also opened campaign with a 2.5-1.5 victory over Sweden.         
	WGM Swati Ghate was the lone winner while D. Harika, Tania Sachdev and Nisha Mohota played out draws. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
